)<br/>≤ 45 % RH @ 40 °C (104 °F) to 50 °C (122 °F)</td></tr><tr><td>Operating altitude</td><td>2000 meters above mean sea level</td></tr><tr><td>Storage altitude</td><td>12,000 meters above mean sea level</td></tr><tr><td>Drop test</td><td>3 meters</td></tr><tr><td>Implement standard</td><td>Q/ASF01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #ccc\"><strong>Standards and agency approval</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Compliance</td><td>IEC 61010-1: Pollution Degree 2</td></tr><tr><td>Laser safety</td><td>IEC 60825-1 Class 2, 650 nm, &lt; 1 mW</td></tr><tr><td>Ingress protection rating</td><td>IP 54 per IEC 60529</td></tr><tr><td>Warranty</td><td>3 years</td></tr></tbody></table></div>', '2023-05-12 18:07:33', 'The HVAC Troubleshooting KitThe most rugged Fluke 62 MAX+ IR thermometer teamed with the easy-to-use 417D Laser Distance Meter has everything you need to configure HVAC layouts and troubleshoot electrical problems. For electrical devices use the IR thermometer to test overheating issues and for HVAC layout, use the 417D to configure layout distance or area and use continuous measurement for marking references.Fluke 417D Laser Distance Meter Additional Features:Continuous measurement capable: adjusting as you move closer and farther from your targetQuickly calculate area (sq. feet/meters)1-meter drop tested and IP54 rated: built to withstand rainy or dusty conditionsGreat for interior and exterior applicationsFluke 62 MAX+ IR Thermometer Additional Features:Dust and water-resistant: IP54 ratedRugged: 3-meter (9.8-foot) drop testedErgonomically designed: Completely redesigned for a more natural hand fitLarge, backlit display: Makes data easier to read, even in dark areas', NULL, NULL),
