e or the connection of a reference test instrument. Maximum working pressure is 10,000 psi (700 bar).', '<div id=\"specification_content\"><div class=\"clickability\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Specifications</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 35%;\">Body Material</td><td>Brass and Stainless steel</td></tr><tr><td>O-Rings</td><td>Nitrile</td></tr><tr><td>Test Port Adapters</td><td>1 set, 1/8, 1/4, 3/8 and 1/2 NPT or BSP and adapters supplied with calibrator</td></tr><tr><td>Calibrator Test Connection</td><td>1/2 BSP male (mating adapter supplied)</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>', '2023-05-12 18:07:33', 'This adapter mounts directly to the test port of the calibrator and allows for the calibration of two instruments at the same time or the connection of a reference test instrument. Maximum working pressure is 10,000 psi (700 bar).', NULL, NULL),
